  "Water becomes denser when a large object is placed on its surface in the ocean": "",
  "Ships are not actually touching the water; they hover slightly above the surface": "",
  "The ship's hollow shape encloses a large volume of air, making the overall density (steel + air) less than water. The ship displaces enough water for the buoyant force to support its weight.": "",
  "A student has two objects with the same mass of 100 g. Object A has a volume of 50 cm³ and Object B has a volume of 25 cm³. Which object would sink faster if dropped in water?": "",
